  <script>
    document.getElementById('area-tabs')?.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
      const btn = (e.target as HTMLElement).closest('[data-filter]') as HTMLElement;
      if (!btn) return;
      const filter = btn.dataset.filter;
      document.querySelectorAll('.area-tab').forEach(t => {
        const el = t as HTMLElement;
        el.style.color = '#999999';
        el.style.background = 'transparent';
        el.style.borderBottom = '2px solid transparent';
        el.style.border = '1px solid transparent';
        el.classList.remove('area-tab--active');
      });
      btn.style.color = '#3D5A3E';
      btn.style.background = '#F9F7F4';
      btn.style.borderBottom = '2px solid #3D5A3E';
      btn.style.border = '1px solid #E5E0D8';
      btn.classList.add('area-tab--active');
      let num = 1;
      document.querySelectorAll('#ranked-table tbody tr').forEach(row => {
        const el = row as HTMLElement;
        if (filter === 'all' || el.dataset.authority === filter) {
          el.style.display = '';
          const numCell = el.querySelector('.row-num') as HTMLElement;
          if (numCell) numCell.textContent = String(num++);
        } else {
          el.style.display = 'none';
        }
      });
    });

    // Ward filter: search + price slider
    const wardSearch = document.getElementById('ward-search') as HTMLInputElement;
    const wardRange = document.getElementById('ward-price-range') as HTMLInputElement;
    const wardLabel = document.getElementById('ward-price-label');
    const wardCount = document.getElementById('ward-count');
    const wardCards = document.querySelectorAll('.ward-card');
    const totalWards = wardCards.length;

    function formatPrice(v: number) {
      return v >= 500000 ? '£500k+' : '£' + Math.round(v / 1000) + 'k';
    }

    function filterWards() {
      const q = wardSearch?.value.toLowerCase() || '';
      const maxPrice = parseInt(wardRange?.value || '500000');
      if (wardLabel) wardLabel.textContent = formatPrice(maxPrice);
      let shown = 0;
      wardCards.forEach(card => {
        const el = card as HTMLElement;
        const price = parseInt(el.dataset.price || '0');
        const name = el.dataset.name || '';
        const type = el.dataset.type || '';
        const matchText = !q || name.includes(q) || type.includes(q);
        const matchPrice = maxPrice >= 500000 || price <= maxPrice;
        if (matchText && matchPrice) {
          el.style.display = '';
          shown++;
        } else {
          el.style.display = 'none';
        }
      });
      if (wardCount) wardCount.textContent = `Showing ${shown} of ${totalWards} Cheshire West wards`;
    }

    wardSearch?.addEventListener('input', filterWards);
    wardRange?.addEventListener('input', filterWards);

    // Scroll hint: hide label when scrolled to end or no overflow
    document.querySelectorAll('.scroll-wrap').forEach(wrapper => {
      const el = wrapper as HTMLElement;
      const label = el.previousElementSibling as HTMLElement;
      if (!label || !label.classList.contains('scroll-hint-label')) return;
      el.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
        if (el.scrollLeft + el.clientWidth >= el.scrollWidth - 8) {
          label.classList.add('hidden');
        } else {
          label.classList.remove('hidden');
        }
      });
      requestAnimationFrame(() => {
        if (el.scrollWidth <= el.clientWidth + 2) {
          label.classList.add('hidden');
        }
      });
    });
  </script>

  <!-- Neighbouring Counties Comparison -->
  <section id="vs-neighbours" class="section-pad">
    <div class="section-inner" style="max-width: 900px;">
      <span class="section-label">Cheshire vs neighbouring counties</span>
      <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.25; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">How do Cheshire house prices compare to neighbouring counties?</h2>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Cheshire averages £314,000 (PlumPlot/ONS, 2025), £92,000 above Merseyside at £222,000 and £105,000 above Lancashire at £209,000. Cheshire ranks 26th of 55 English and Welsh counties by average price (PlumPlot, 2025). Move to Cheshire calculates a population-weighted authority average of £274,250 for the four Cheshire unitary authorities (ONS Dec 2025, Census 2021 populations), which sits between the PlumPlot aggregate and the individual ONS figures.</p>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 28px 0;">Two neighbouring areas exceed the Cheshire county average: Trafford in Greater Manchester at £378,094 (ONS, Aug 2025) and Derbyshire Dales at £339,448. Both are localised premiums within otherwise cheaper counties. Even using the lower population-weighted figure of £274,250, Cheshire remains £52,000 above Merseyside, £65,000 above Lancashire, and £40,000 above Derbyshire overall. Cheshire East at £302,000-£306,000 (ONS Aug-Dec 2025) is the most consistently expensive authority across the North West and bordering Midlands.</p>
      <span class="scroll-hint-label">&larr; &rarr; Scroll for more columns</span>
      <div class="scroll-wrap" style="overflow-x: auto; -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch; margin-bottom: 28px;">
        <table class="neighbours-table" style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; min-width: 420px;">
          <thead>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 2px solid #3D5A3E;">
              <th style="text-align: left; padding: 12px; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: #1C1C1E;">County / Region</th>
              <th style="text-align: left; padding: 12px; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: #1C1C1E;">Average</th>
              <th style="text-align: left; padding: 12px; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: #1C1C1E;" class="hide-mobile">Range</th>
              <th style="text-align: left; padding: 12px; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: #1C1C1E;" class="hide-mobile">Premium Area</th>
              <th style="text-align: left; padding: 12px; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: #1C1C1E;" class="hide-narrow">Source</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {neighbours.map((n, i) => (
              <tr style={`background-color: ${i % 2 === 0 ? '#FFFFFF' : '#F9F7F4'}; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E0D8; ${i === 0 ? 'border-left: 3px solid #3D5A3E;' : ''}`}>
                <td style={`padding: 14px 12px; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: ${i === 0 ? '700' : '600'}; color: #1C1C1E;`}>{n.name}</td>
                <td style={`padding: 14px 12px; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; color: ${i === 0 ? '#3D5A3E' : '#444444'};`}>{n.avg}</td>
                <td style="padding: 14px 12px; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; color: #444444;" class="hide-mobile">{n.range}</td>
                <td style="padding: 14px 12px; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; color: #444444;" class="hide-mobile">{n.premium}</td>
                <td style="padding: 14px 12px; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; color: #999999;" class="hide-narrow">{n.source}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="margin-top: 20px; border-left: 3px solid #C4933F; background-color: rgba(196, 147, 63, 0.04); padding: 20px 24px;">
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; color: #C4933F; margin: 0 0 8px 0; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em;">Move to Cheshire methodology</p>
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 12px 0;"><strong>The problem:</strong> No single official source publishes a "Cheshire house price." PlumPlot aggregates all authorities within the ceremonial county boundary and reports £314,000 (2025). ONS UK HPI reports individual authority averages - Cheshire East at £306,000 and CW&C at £266,000 (Dec 2025) - but publishes no county-level figure. The same issue affects Greater Manchester (10 boroughs, no single average) and Lancashire (PlumPlot £209,000 vs ONS £186,000 for the local authority area only, excluding Blackburn, Blackpool, and Burnley unitaries).</p>
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 12px 0;"><strong>Our formula:</strong> Move to Cheshire calculates a population-weighted authority average using ONS UK HPI prices and Census 2021 populations. The formula weights each authority's average price by its share of the total Cheshire population: (CE price x CE pop + CW&C price x CW&C pop + Warrington price x Warrington pop + Halton price x Halton pop) / total Cheshire pop. This produces £274,250 - lower than PlumPlot's £314,000 because it accounts for Halton (pop. 128,500) and Warrington (pop. 209,500) pulling the weighted average below the Cheshire East figure.</p>
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: #444444; margin: 0;"><strong>Which figure to use:</strong> The table above shows both the established PlumPlot/ONS aggregates and the min-max range for each county. The range column is the most reliable comparison because it reveals the spread within each area. A single "average" for Greater Manchester (£190,000-£378,000) or Cheshire (£189,000-£306,000 by authority, £115,000-£666,000 by town) conceals more than it reveals.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
