      <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.25; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">Where can I find more detailed Cheshire house price data?</h2>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 28px 0;">Cheshire house prices on this page cover four authorities, 41 towns, and 35 wards. Four deeper guides break down individual Cheshire house price topics - town-level street data, property type splits, stamp duty calculations at Cheshire price points, and whether 2026 market conditions favour buying.</p>
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 16px;">
        {spokeCards.map((card) => (
          <a href={card.href} class="pillar-card" style="text-decoration: none; display: block;">
            <h3 style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0 0 8px 0; line-height: 1.3;">{card.title}</h3>
            <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; color: #999999; margin: 0;">{card.description}</p>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Good to Know -->
  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="section-inner" style="max-width: 720px;">
      <div id="methodology" style="border-left: 3px solid #3D5A3E; background-color: rgba(61, 90, 62, 0.04); padding: 24px 28px;">
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; color: #3D5A3E; margin: 0 0 12px 0; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em;">How did Move to Cheshire build this Cheshire house price page?</p>
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">
          <strong>Move to Cheshire cross-references three Cheshire house price sources that no single provider combines.</strong> ONS reports authority-level averages but publishes no Cheshire county figure. Rightmove covers individual Cheshire towns but uses asking prices. CW&C Council ward data captures hyper-local Cheshire West medians but lags by two years. This page merges all three into a single verifiable view - from the £314,000 county average down to £115,000 in Ellesmere Port Westminster ward.
        </p>
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">
          <strong>Three sources, structured by geographic level.</strong> ONS UK HPI (December 2025) provides the four authority averages: Cheshire East £306,000, Cheshire West £266,000, Warrington £252,000, Halton £189,000. Rightmove (12 months to February 2026) provides Golden Triangle and Cheshire East town prices. CW&C Council (2023) provides the 35 ward-level medians. ONS figures lag 2-3 months due to Land Registry registration delays. Rightmove asking prices run 3-5% above completed transaction prices.
        </p>
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">
          <strong>Cheshire's housing stock skews the average upward.</strong> Detached homes represent 34% of Cheshire housing stock versus 22% nationally (Census 2021). Cheshire detached homes average £496,000 (ONS, Dec 2025), pulling the county mean above areas with higher terraced and flat proportions.
        </p>
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; color: #444444; margin: 0;">
          <strong>Price alone does not determine value.</strong> Cheshire house prices vary by <a href="/where-to-live/best-places-cheshire/" class="green-cta-link">area character and lifestyle fit</a>, proximity to <a href="/schools/" class="green-cta-link">Outstanding-rated schools</a> (112 across the county, Ofsted 2024/25), and <a href="/commuting/" class="green-cta-link">Manchester commute time</a> (17-55 minutes by rail). Buyers weighing Cheshire against other regions can compare <a href="/lifestyle/pros-cons-living-cheshire/" class="green-cta-link">pros and cons of living in Cheshire</a> and <a href="/lifestyle/is-cheshire-safe/" class="green-cta-link">Cheshire crime rates</a> alongside price data.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related Hubs -->
  <section class="section-pad" style="background-color: #FFFFFF; border-top: 1px solid #E5E0D8;">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-label">Beyond Cheshire house prices</span>
      <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.25; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">What else affects where to buy in Cheshire?</h2>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 28px 0;">Cheshire house prices range from £115,000 to £666,000 across the county, but the right purchase depends on more than price. School catchments add 10-20% to property values in Wilmslow and Knutsford. A 17-minute commute from Wilmslow commands a £230,000 premium over a 55-minute commute from Crewe. Three guides cover the factors that shape where the price data points you.</p>
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 16px;">
